\is1 Introduction
\ip Tsefanyah (commonly known as Zephaniah) was a prophet of time Husiyas the King of Yehudah. Tutubungi them and served of Master God. But of not/none long time, in-engkeran their e the Master and is their e serving the false gods. So then the threatened e the Master punished din the ones from-Yehudah and the ones from-Yerushalem due to evil me deeds their. But even then, not/none them requested of forgiveness him. Sikan naa, of 586 year(s) of not yet born the Messiah, indereetan of me from-Babylon the Yerushalem. But even then, migpahunlibet just he egtalipunen din just them keureme from nations engkeranslaved them. And/Now return din just them there to Yerushalem and egpanalanginan din.
\iot Main components of this “book”
\io1 The time of judging of Master God \ior 1:1–2:3\ior*
\io1 The destruction of nations near Israel \ior 2:4-15\ior*
\io1 The destruction and saving/explaining of Yerushalem \ior 3:1-20\ior*
