\c 1
\p
\v 1 The message from Yahweh which came to Tsefanyah (son of Kush, son of Gedalyah, son of Amaryah, son of Hizkiyyah) in the \add time\add* of Amon’s son, King Yoshiyyah \add (Josiah)\add* of Yehudah \add (Judah)\add*\x + \xo 1:1: \xt 2Ki 22:1–23:30; 2Ch 34:1–35:27.\x*
\s1 The day punishing the master
\p
\v 2 Yahweh declares:
\m I will exterminate everything \add that lives\add* on the ground.
\p
\v 3 Yahweh declares:
\m I’ll bring humans and animals to an end, \add along with\add* the birds and fish. Wicked \add people\add* \add will be destroyed along with their idols\add* and humankind will be cut-off from the earth.
\v 4 I will \add punish\add* \add the people of\add* Yehudah,
\q1 and those living in Yerushalem.
\q1 I will \add wipe\add* all remnants of Baal out from this place.
\q1 \add No one will even remember\add* the names of those priests \add who served idols\add*.
\q1
\v 5 \add I’ll punish\add* those who bowed down to the \add stars and planets\add* from their rooftops,
\q1 and those making promises to Yahweh but then promising to \add the false god\add* Milcom.\f + \fr 1:5 \ft A variant of the name of the pagan god ‘Molek’ (or ‘Molech’, but also close to the Hebrew word for ‘king’ as found in some other translations).\f*
\q1
\v 6 \add I’ll punish\add* those who turn back after following \add me,\add* Yahweh,
\q1 as well as those who haven’t searched for Yahweh or prayed to \add me\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 7 Be silent in the presence of the master Yahweh,
\q2 because his day is near.
\q1 Yahweh has prepared a sacrifice,
\q2 and he’s consecrated his guests.
\q1
\v 8 On the day of Yahweh’s sacrifice
\q1 I will visit \add their officials\add* and the king’s sons,
\q1 and all those wearing foreign clothing,
